commit.message: scd: return better error if pubkey algo unknown
scd: command: do not leak sexp in keyinfo

scd: command: do not attempt to reference NULL

happens when at cleanup when allocation fails.

scd: command: fix free of not allocated pointer

when timestamp is not provided in genkey command.
gnupg-pkcs11-scd: Fix memory leak in listing certificates

gnupg-pkcs11-scd: command: fix segfault on PKAUTH command

It seems hash value is no longer an empty string but a null pointer, so
the condition must handle it, otherwise it segfaults.

Closes: #39
Signed-off-by: Mateusz Gozdek <mgozdekof@gmail.com>
gnupg-pkcs11-scd: support specific key pin based on pkcs11-helper
gnupg-pkcs11-scd: support gnupg pin cache using the use-gnupg-pin-cache option

gnupg-pkcs11-scd: rework token and pin hooks

use the serialized tokenid as test because gnupg expects single variable (token).

command: readkey: accept also hexgrip for key

gnupg-2.3 regression, sends sometimes the key id and sometimes the hexgrip,
no way to know which.

command: readkey: accept info parameters

Required for gnupg-2.3

command: add keyinfo command

Required for gnupg-2.3

gnupg-pkcs11-scd: use strgetarg for all line arguments

gnupg-2.3 seems to add command arguments for all commands.
misc: openssl: support always-auth and fixup engine
